"Francine and March tried to protect me, but it was too late! The beast knew what chemicals were needed to bring itself about. It was out of my control. And it only needs one more component to complete the process. It's in me, Batman." Today's BTAS episode starts at season 1 episode 1 titled "On Leather Wings" with the main villain being Kirk Langstrom/the Man-Bat. Bruce Timm stated that they decided to do the first episode around a villain that people would not have anything to compare it to, such as the Joker, where everyone would of just critiqued whether it was better then Jack Nicholson or Caesar Romerero's interpretations. They wanted to let their work, story telling, and art be the focal point. We even get to see a Batman that the GCPD is still at odds with, not knowing if he's a friend or foe. The animation in this really set the tone for the whole series and separated itself from anything that had been done before or since. Although this was the first episode produced, and officially the "pilot" the first episode to air was "Cat and the Claw: part 1". The reasoning for this was so fans could see a character they just recently saw in Batman Returns in Catwoman. All in all any fan of this show has a special place in their heart for this episode. Hope you guys enjoy these post, thos might be the last time doing these photos! "It's the Awful Lawful Family!" next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Christmas with the Joker". It's now a  Christmas staple that sees the Joker breakout of Arkham Asylum on Christmas Eve while singing the now famous "Jingle Bells Batman smells". Batman and Robin catch wind of his escape and go looking for him, but Robin tries convincing his partner there's no way anyone would commit a crime on Christmas Eve. Eventually Batman relents and they go home to watch "It's a Wonderful Life" but instead they see the Clown Prince of Crime doing his own Christmas Special! He's got Gordon, Bullock, and Summer Gleeson all bound and is threatening to kill them if the dynamic duo can't reach him on time. It's a superb episode that even plays some Nutcracker music to Batman hitting toy planes!  Hamill is, of course, on his game throughout voicing Mr. J with maniacal glee, openly mocking Gleeson for crying due to her mom being on a train the Joker is about to blow up. "Remember what you told me? You can't lose hope.." Today's BTAS episode is from season 1 the 8th to be produced and 23rd to air. We start off with Bruce volunteering his time to feed homeless at the dock rescue mission, which he also gives money too. As he's working, a priest mentions that a lot of homeless are missing. Bruce decides to investigate, dying his hair gray, and growing out some stuble he assimilates himself into the homeless community and starts asking questions. Before he knows it he's knocked out and taken to a chain gang camp where Boss Biggis runs a brutal business, using these slaves for cheap labor. Bruce has amnesia and has totally forgotten who he even is! He struggles with this identity lose while trying to get used to the slave labor. He has a dream one night where he's walking down a hall and the Joker grabs him and they fall off a building. Then his dream takes him to the dock rescue mission. He walks the street as Bruce Wayne and a homeless man comes up and ask for a few bucks, so he obliges. Then a few more homeless come and he keeps handing out money generously until he's overwhelmed by beggars and he slumps his shoulders..shedding a tear. Knowing that as much as he can do, it's barely enough to help. It's quite a striking visual and in media we see Batman as a loner, or someone that doesn't love people. On the contrary, this episode shows Bruce has a huge heart for those less fortunate than himself and he strives to help them. Again, it's one I wasn't fond of as a child, because he's barely in costume and no big rogues villain. The writing, striking visuals, and different way of telling this story makes it a winner in my book now. Hope you guys enjoy these episode shots, have a great day. #theforgotten #forgotten #brucewayne #alfredpennyworth #bossbiggis #homelessness #homless #dcdirect #dccollectibles #ready_setz  #dcanimateduniverse #dcanimation #dcau #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #batmantheadventurescontinue #brucewayne #brucetimm #pauldini #kevinconroy #tylergshow #thetylergshow #arkhamasylum #arkham #batwing

"Take a card, Batso! Take all the cards!"
Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Be A Clown" it was the 9th produced and 11th to air. It features the Joker crashing Mayor Hill's son Jordan's birthday party, the Joker does this because Mayor Hill said Batman and he were the same, plus said his mansion is beyond safe. Joker dresses as Jekko the clown and pretends to entertain the kids long enough to place a dynamite candle on the cake. We again too see Bruce's caring side as he wants most to help Harvey above all else. One of the most iconic Batman two parters for sure and rewatching it only confirms it holds up now more than ever. Commissioner Gordon: "Poor Harvey, so filled with anger. Do you think there's any hope?

Batman: "Where there's love, there's hope, Commissioner. But a little luck wouldn't hurt. For you Harvey." 

Today's double feature BTAS shot is continuing with the 11th episode produced and 18th to air, "Two Face: Prt.2" Harvey is in full on revenge mode against Thorne, stealing all he can from him as a way to taunt him before he decides he's going to end him once and for all. Meanwhile we see Batman/Bruce having night terrors of Harvey telling him "You could of saved me..now look at me!" We even see his parents say the same thing before Bruce wakes in a panic. You can tell Bruce is going through mental torment. Harvey decides he wants to see his fiancé Grace, but earlier in the episode we see Candice (Thorne's seductive secretary) give Grace a tracker that will lead Thorne to Harvey. We see a good bad ugly style standoff between Harvey, Thorne, and Batman. Thorne gets taken care of and Batman is struggling. Two-Face has the upper hand...but Batman incapacitated him by throwing a box of coins at him as Harvey flipped his. You see Two-Face utterly paralyzed by the anxiety of losing the coin and watch his descent into madness while he looks screaming from the top of his lungs. Think of it, Batman. To never again walk on a summer's day with the hot wind in your face and a warm hand to hold. Oh yes, I'd kill for that!
The next BTAS episode is the 14th produced, 3rd to air, and it needs no introduction, "Heart of Ice". Every so often we as fans of comics and their tie ins get treated to a story that feels bigger then the rest. As Batman fans we've been treated to a lot, Death in the Family, Killing Joke, Knightfall, Dark Knight Returns, Under the Red Hood, Flashpoint, Endgame, etc, you catch my drift... stories that are game changers. Well, when you mention Batman the Animated Series, outside of Kevin Conroy and Mark Hamill's perfect portrayals of their characters, I'm pretty sure most fans have this episode come to mind. It's a beautifully haunting tragedy of a man who unfairly lost his wife and just wanted to save her. I think when this episode aired every one stopped and took notice that this show was not some silly thing for kids, but was meant to be something more and stand the test of time, which it has. It's not my personal favorite, but I can't deny it's almost a perfect episode and reinvigorated a character most thought idiotic. I hope you enjoy your day! #heartofice #victorfries #norafries #mrfreeze #batman #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcuniverse  #dcmultiverse #dcicons #dcrebirth #dcanimation #dcau #dceu #dcessentials #dc #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham #bigbadtoystore #batmantheadventurescontinue #soapstudioshk

"You can't deny there's something between us." Today's BTAS episode is from season 1, the 1st episode to air and 15th produced and is part one of two, titled "The Cat and the Claw". We start off with  Catwoman breaking into someone's house and using her cat to get some jewels. However, Batman shows up and they have their first chase across the roofs of Gotham. Catwoman skips away but they know they'll see each other again. Catwoman is made out to be a big animal rights activist in this episode and she's trying to create a wild life preserve compound but is finding it difficult. She goes on a date with Bruce and even uses his connections to get a meeting with a company competing with her for land she wants to build the preserve on. Once in the building she takes note of how she can get in. She cuts the date short and decides to come back as Catwoman, meanwhile Bruce decides to get costumed up as well. Selina breaks in and finds out the business is a front for the terrorist group run by "Red Claw". We discover Red Claw is one of the most dangerous women on the planet and she now wants Catwoman dead. Catwoman has the full attention of the terrorist group now and almost escapes but starts to fall from a building when Batman gets her. While swinging to safety Catwoman gives him a kiss as a thank you. Catwoman: "So, you do care."

Today's episode is from season 1 and is part 2 from "Cat and the Claw", it was the 8th episode to air and 16th produced. The episode starts with Batman hearing rumors of Red Claw taking over a train to steal a deadly plague she can use to hold the city ransom. Red Claw and her crew get the plague despite Batman showing up. At the end of the first part of this episode we saw Red Claw knows Catwoman is Selina Kyle after they followed her home once she broke into their facilities. We see Red Claw's gang terrorize Selina Kyle while she's on a date with Bruce and mess with her roommate. After the attack on the date and finding Isis hair, Batman figures out who Selina really is. Catwoman goes to Red Claws facilities to get evidence of her plan and stop her but she gets caught. Batman saves her but they both get captured and tied up. Red Claw leaves the real plague being eaten away by acid and soon to be released with Batman and Catwoman, saying she'll  just trick Gotham and once she gets her 10 billion dollars, escape before they realize it's fake. However, Batman alerted the GCPD and they are waiting outside for the terrorist group. Batman and Catwoman escape while blowing up the plague and everything inside with it. Batman: Ventrix, the suit! It's poison!

Lloyd Ventrix: So what if it is? I don't care! As long as I have it, I can take my daughter back whenever I want! Her mother won't be able to stop me, and neither will you!

Today's BTAS episode is from season 1 titled "See No Evil" it was the 56th to air but 17th to be produced. The episode starts with us seeing a an invisible man go into a little girl named Kimmy's bedroom. She greets him as Mojo and they talk, "Mojo" says he'll see her soon but she warns they're moving, and this upsets him. We hear Kimmy's mom coming and Mojo leaves, the mother thinks the daughter really has an imaginary friend so she pays her no mind. We then see the man "Mojo", and his real name is Lloyd Ventrix. He puts on this silver suit, hits a button turning invisible and then proceeds to rob a jewelry store. Bruce is there and quickly changes into Batman and then goes after the invisible man. He is able to find a few tricks in order to see Lloyds silhouette, but the invisibility is too much for Batman as he gets whooped. Llyod escapes to rob another day. Batman does some digging to find out who the man is, and in the process learns the plastic that makes the plastic invisible is also highly toxic to the wearer. Batman goes after Lloyd as he is abducting Kimmy who we learn is his daughter, and his ex-wife has a restraining order on him as well. Batman confronts him and is able to take him down while keeping Kimmy safe. Very cool and different episode, crazy to see how an ordinary guy in an invisibility suit can give Batman so much trouble. #seenoevil #lloydventrix #cloakofinvisibility #invisibilitycloak #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #batmantheadventurescontinue #brucetimm #pauldini #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcanimation #dcau #dcicons #dcrebirth #dcanimateduniverse #dc #bigbadtoystore #beastkingdom #soapstudioshk #mcfarlanemultiverse #mcfarlane #mattelmultiverse #mattel

“When crime haunts the night, a silent crusader carries the torch of justice. Those with evil hearts beware for out of the darkness comes the Gray Ghost!” Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Beware the Gray Ghost" it was the 18th produced and 32nd to air. Masterpiece, this episode is that, in my eyes. Anytime we get a glimpse into Batman's past or childhood it's cool, because we still have not seen that too much, at least at the point in time this aired. We see a very meta scene where we are watching Bruce Wayne and his father watch their favorite hero on TV, The Gray Ghost! This scene alone is amazing to me. We already love Batman because we can relate to him, and here we see he's a lot more like us then we initially ever thought. The story progresses to where Bruce, as Batman, gets to meet and help his hero in real life, Simon Trent aka the Gray Ghost. Adam West voices the Gray Ghost, and if you know anything about his life you can see this episode does not try to hide the parallels of reality and fiction when it comes to West's struggle to find work after being type cast as only Batman. This is indeed a crown jewel for this series and another example of how this show elevated itself beyond the norm of what everyone else was doing at the time. If you haven't seen this and you are a Batman fan, it is a must, go see this now. #bewarethegrayghost #grayghost #simontrent #adamwest #dcdirect #dccollectibles #dcanimateduniverse #dcanimation #dcau #dcuniverse #dcmultiverse #commisionergordon #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #batmantheadventurescontinue #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham  #bigbadtoystore #soapstudioshk #arkhamknight #mcfarlanemultiverse #mattel

"We are but radios for the cosmic transmitter, tune your receivers, hear the inner voice!..." The next BTAS shot is from season 1 episode 19 to be produced and 22 to air, titled "Prophecy of Doom". In this episode we see Bruce invited to witness a cult like leader speaking to a bunch of his rich friends. His name is Nostromos, and he has convinced a lot of Gotham's wealthy men and women that he knows the world will end soon and he can offer them protection. Bruce doesn't buy it but with a lot of random crimes going on he decides to play along and see what he can find out. He pretends to "See the light" and he gets to hear and see more of Nostromos' plan. However, Nostromos starts his plan early and convinces his rich clients to sign over their fortune to him after he says the world will end soon. Batman comes to the rescue and easily handles the whole situation. The main villain always looked a lot like Ras Al Ghul to me, in fact I remember thinking it was going to be revealed it was him, but alas, he was a one off villain. The Joker: Hello, Charlie.

Charlie Collins: Wrong number, pal. My name's Don.

The Joker: Oh, no, no, no. This *is* the right number, Charles Michael Collins. Oh, I don't know why you changed your name to Don Wallace and moved your family to 12 Marigold Lane, Springdale, Ohio. One might think you were trying to skip out on our little deal.

Today's BTAS episode is from season 1, it was the 7th to air and 22nd produced, titled "Joker's Favor". The episode begins with us seeing Charlie Collins, an average man, driving home from work and complaining about how he never gets taken seriously, then we see him get cut off on the freeway. This pushes him right over the edge and he goes speeding after the car waving his fist and chewing out the driver. Then he sees that the driver is the Joker! He goes speeding away trying to hide from the Clown Prince but Mr. J finds him. Joker let's him live but only after he gets his information and drivers license saying he'll call him with a favor at anytime. Charlie gets away and enters the witness protection program changing his name and living happily with his family until he gets a phone call from Joker saying it's time for that favor. From there the episode just continues to get better and better. This one is also famous for being the first ever appearance of Harley Quinn! Today's BTAS episode is from season 1, it was the 7th to air and 22nd produced, titled "Joker's Favor". The episode begins with us seeing Charlie Collins, an average man, driving home from work and complaining about how he never gets taken seriously, then we see him get cut off on the freeway. This pushes him right over the edge and he goes speeding after the car waving his fist and chewing out the driver. Then he sees that the driver is the Joker! He goes speeding away trying to hide from the Clown Prince but Mr. J finds him. Joker let's him live but only after he gets his information and drivers license saying he'll call him with a favor at anytime. Charlie gets away and enters the witness protection program changing his name and living happily with his family until he gets a phone call from Joker saying it's time for that favor. From there the episode just continues to get better and better. This one is also famous for being the first ever appearance of Harley Quinn! "This ain't no Batcave." The next BTAS episode is from season 1 titled "Vendetta" and is the 23rd produced and 21st to air. Criminals are starting to be kidnapped and no ones got a clue who's doing it. Batman starts to investigate the areas where people are missing and starts to get a lot of clues pointing to Harvey Bullock. Then "Bullock" breaks into secret files he wouldn't have access to and the next day he is arrested. Batman isn't content however, and feels it was someone else. He does DNA testing on a scale he found that has both human and crocodile properties. He learns about a wrestler named "Killer Croc" who hasn't been heard from in a while and eventually finds his underwater cavern with the kidnapped criminals. Batman is able to get the men to safety and away from Croc. Batman uses Bullock as bait to draw Croc out and they have an epic battle in Gotham's sewers. I love this episode and especially the original design of Croc.  #harveybullock #killercroc #croc #waylonjones #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcuniverse #dcmultiverse #dcicons #dcrebirth #dcanimation #dcau #dcdirect #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #batmantheadventurescontinue #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham #bigbadtoystore #mcfarlanemultiverse #soapstudioshk #gcpd #dioramaprints

"Good people still live in Crime Alley." The next  BTAS episode is from season 1 titled "Appointment in Crime Alley" and it was 12th to air but 26th produced. Batman took on gentrification long before the hipsters started taking over Brooklyn. In this episode Roland Daggett wants to destroy crime alley so he can get all the poor people and business' out of there and build up his business in their place. He hires an arsonist named Nitro to do the job, severing himself from guilt. He also starts sending flunkies around Crime Alley telling people to clear out, Batman arrives to prevent two thugs from harassing a mom and girl. He learns about them strong arming people out and does more investigation on who hired them. The whole reason Batman was in Crime Alley was for an appointment with Dr. Leslie Thompkins, she notices he's late so goes looking for him but accidentally sees Nitro the arsonist and crew about to start burning down everything. She speaks up, confronting them and is immediately tied up to a chair in a room full of explosives. Batman finds out Thompkins is missing while looking for him so he goes for her by heading to her house. There he finds a scrapbook of his parents murder, with a picture of Dr. Thompkins holding and comforting a young, devastated Bruce. Nitro does start to burn some buildings but nothing great and is stopped by Batman easily, he confesses who he's working for, but Daggett gets off, he's too powerful. Batman decides he will let this go for now, as he meets up with Dr. Thompkins and they visit Bruce's parents murder site, the episode closes with Leslie comforting Bruce again as they remember Thomas and Martha. #appointmentincrimealley #rolanddaggett #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcanimation #dcanimateduniverse #dcau #dcicons #dcrebirth #dceu #lesliethompkins #thomaswayne #marthawayne #thomasandmarthawayne #crimealley #brucewayne #brucetimm #pauldini #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham #bigbadtoystore #soapstudioshk #dioramaprints

The Mad Hatter: I'll cut that cowl off your neck before you take her! I've waited my whole lonely life for her!

Batman: Then all you've waited for is a puppet... a soulless little doll.

The next BTAS shot is from season 1 titled "Mad as a Hatter" it was the 24th to air and 27th produced. It starts off with us seeing Jervis Tetch, a timid scientist controlling mice with his new mind controlling technology. He's interrupted by Alice, the Secretary, warning the the big bosses are coming which is Bruce and Marcia Cates, so he hides his work. He's chided by Tates for not having all his work ready to present to Mr. Wayne,  Alice cheers him up and mentions her boyfriend. Tetch has a crush and Alice, he goes back and forth on whether or not he should use his mind control on her but decides against it. He hears Alice crying and comes to find her boyfriend called it off, so he takes her out yo cheer her up and uses mind control on others around town to make himself look hood and get VIP treatment at restaurants and such. However, the next day when Jervis heads into his office he hears the Alice is not only back with her boyfriend but now engaged. This sends Tetch over the edge and we see his descent down the rabbit hole as he becomes...the Mad Hatter. #jervistetch #themadhatter #madhatter #madasahatter #lewiscarroll #aliceinwonderland #mindcontrol #teaparty #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcuniverse #dcmultiverse #dcicons #dcrebirth #dcanimation #dcanimation #dcdirect #batmantheadventurescontinue #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham #mcfarlanemultiverse #soapstudioshk #bigbadtoystore

 Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Robin's Reckoning prt. 1" it was the 31st episode produced and 51st to air. This is lot of fans favorite episode and it's a great Robin story. "I've waited a loooong time." The next BTAS episode is titled "Robin's Reckoning Part 2" it's the 32nd/33rd to be produced and 51st/53rd to air. In this episode we see the origin of Robin/ Dick Grayson. We see his parents death at the hands of Tony Zucco at Haley's Circus. Bruce happened to be in attendance and decided he was going to adopt young Grayson. We see Bruce eventually reveal he's Batman and start the relationship of the original dynamic duo. Only one problem, Bruce has hidden who killed Robins parents from Dick to protect him from acting out violently in a rage towards the man and do something he would regret. Robin finds this out though while being left behind and goes after Zucco himself. He eventually finds him and the scene is filled with emotion. You see Robin in full on wreck mode as he drags Zuccos body like a rag doll while on his motorcycle. He then whoops him up a bit then dangles him near the edge of a pier. As he speaks you hear pure anger/rage as he looks into the fearful eyes of his parents murderer. One more push and he could end Zucco, but Batman gets to him and talks him out of his emotional rage. The episode ends with Zucco in jail and Robin doing the right thing. It's a well crafted, emotional episode that is beautifully done because it wasn't rushed and they expanded it to the two parts, highly recommended this one. #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcuniverse #dcmultiverse #dcanimation #dcanimateduniverse #dcau #dc #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #robinsreckoning #robinsreckoningpart2 #tonyzucco #thedynamicduo #dynamicduo #batmanandrobin #dickgrayson #theflyinggraysons #robin #theboywonder #boywonder #brucetimm #pauldini #bigbadtoystore

Jason Todd: Ignoring what he's done in the past. Blindly, stupidly disregarding the entire graveyards he's filled, the thousands who have suffered, the friends he's crippled. You know, I thought... I thought I'd be the last person you'd ever let him hurt. If it had been you that he beat to a bloody pulp, if he had taken you from this world, I would've done nothing but search the planet for this pathetic pile of evil, death-worshiping garbage and then send him off to hell!

Batman: You don't understand. I don't think you've ever understood.

Jason Todd: What? That your moral code just won't allow for that? It's too hard to cross that line?

Batman: No! God Almighty, no. It'd be too damned easy. All I've ever wanted to do is kill him. A day doesn't go by that I don't think about subjecting him to every horrendous torture he's dealt out to others, and then... end him.

Joker: Aw, so you *do* think about me.

Batman: But if I do that, if I allow myself to go down into that place... I'll never come back.

Jason Todd: Why? I'm not talking about killing Penguin or Scarecrow or Dent. I'm talking about *him*, just him. And doing it because... because he took me away from you.

Batman: I can't. I'm sorry.

Joker: That is so sweet!

"You're really sick you know that boss?" Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "The Laughing Fish" it is the 34th produced and 46th to air. This episode is an adaptation from  the famous story, "The Joker's Five-Way Revenge"  from Batman #251, September 1973 by Dennis O'Neil, "The Laughing Fish" and "Sign of the Joker!" from Detective Comics #475/476, February/March 1978 by Steve Englehart. "So, the famous Batman, I am honored!" Today's BTAS episode is titled "Night of the Ninja" it was 35th produced and 28th to make air. Wayne Entriprises has been a major target of thefts all the sudden, being attacked often and Batman decides he's going to find out who's helping themselves. He comes to find a Ninja, that he takes on and is beating until he fights dirty, Batman is almost taken out until Robin saves him. During the fight the Ninja suffered a tear in the back of his shirt and Bruce  clearly sees the tattoo of his rival from when he trained in Japan. His name is Kyodai Ken, he was superior to Bruce back then and regularly beat him in sparring matches. One night while training late Bruce caught Kyodai trying to steal from the sensai, this caused Kyodai great shame and he was kicked out, he vowed vengeance on Bruce...and all these years later he is getting it. Kyodai kidnaps Bruce and Summer Gleeson spelling out his plan. He fights Bruce but Bruce holds back in front of Summer, taking a major beating to hide the fact he's Batman. Robin shows up, covers Gleeson's face and Bruce proceeds to completely dominate Kyodai. Kyodai manages to get away, and we will see him again later. This is a great episode because it showed us Bruce's training long before Batman Begins did the same and it's always fun seeing that aspect of the Batman. #nightoftheninja #kyodaiken #japan #batmanbegins #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #dccollectibles #dcanimation #dcau #dcdirect #dccomics #dcrebirth #dc #ninja #batmanandrobin #dickgrayson #robin #bigbadtoystore #soapstudioshk #beastkingdom #brucetimm #pauldini

Amanda Waller: I've known Bruce Wayne for over 50 years, and I've kept an eye on you your whole life. You're not Bruce's clone, you're his son. There are similarities, mind you, but more than a few differences too. You don't quite have his magnificent brain, for instance. You do have his heart, though. And for all that fierce exterior, I've never met anyone who cared as deeply about his fellow man as Bruce Wayne, except maybe you. You want to have a little better life than the old man's? Take care of the people who love you. Or don't. It's your choice.

"Try your luck, friend?" 
Today's BTAS shot is from the episode "Jokers Wild" it was the 41st produced and 42nd to air. We start off with Joker watching TV with Ivy in Arkham, on the tv there's an unveiling for a new casino, called "Jokers Wild" and the decorations all resemble Joker himself. In fact even the workers are dressed as either Mr. J or Harley! Jokers furious that the owner of the casino, Cameron Kaiser, would try to make money off of his image. So the Joker breaks out intent on ruining the opening. Bruce decides to stay at the casino and look into why Kaiser would purposely open a place like this. He comes to find Kaiser bankrupted himself and is in massive debt trying to build the casino and that originally it was going to be a Camelot theme. Kaiser took an insurance policy out, and changed the theme hoping that the Joker would wreck the place and he'd get his money. It's a very entertaining episode with a great story (written by the great Paul Dini) and one of my favorite moments is when Bruce is out of costume and has a conversation with the Joker while playing blackjack. Selina Kyle: Wait. Won't you come with us? There's nothing for you here.

 Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Tyger Tyger" it was the 30th to air and 42 produced. This episode is my 3rd favorite right behind "Feat of Clay" and "Perchance to Dream". I can watch it multiple times without it ever losing its effectiveness. It's a little strange at first, and many fans are put off by that, but the story and episode itself are beautiful. The visuals, darker tones than usual, and it even takes Batman back to his early comic days taking on mad scientist in huge castles in remote locations. The ending though, the ending.... the last 5 minutes is worth seeing itself. Kevin Conroys voice reciting William Blake's poem "Tyger, Tyger" is something that must be heard. I could go on and on about what I like about it, but you should check it yourself! "The guy had just about everything, and he gives it all up?" Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Moon of the Wolf" it is the 43rd produced and 36th to air. A lot of people would say...Batman vs a Werewolf? Is this a joke? This episode is actually based on a comic, Batman issue #255 which was written by Len Wein and penciled by Neal Adams! It Really is another good, yet underrated story of a man who was an Olympic Athlete, Anthony Romulus, and he loves being in the limelight as well as living the celebrity life, but as all athletes do, he starts to age as time wears on. He decides to stay on top he'll need help, and he gets it from the evil Dr. Milo. Milo uses a steroid werewolf formula which allows him to use the werewolf side as a slave to do his bidding. Milo realizes only Batman can stop his plans so he has Romulus take on the bat saying he'll cure him if he does. It's definitely different from the usual, but also very cool to see a an episode based on an old Batman v monster comic. "You are strong..but not strong enough! Farewell Batman!" Today's BTAS shot is from season 2 episode 16 titled "Day of the Samurai". We are taken to Japan to the dojo of Yoru Sensei, a man Bruce trained under. Here we see a young female named Kairi Tanaka, as she practices a ninja appears, knocks her out and drags her away, but while leaving a ransom letter for the Sensei. Naturally Yoru calls Wayne asking for aid, so he and Alfred pack their bags to help Bruce's old Sensei. Once there Bruce learns that Kyodai l, his former nemesis at the dojo is behind all this. He doesn't want money, he desires Yoru to teach him or give him instructions on "Kiba no Hoko" an ancient but deadly martial art taught to a select few. Batman delivers the map but Kyodai kicks Kairi off a ledge forcing Batman to save her and allowing Kyodai to flee. Kyodai finds the ancient scroll with instructions on Kiba no Hoko, but most of it is gone due to age, however he is able to learn a few things. He kidnaps Alfred in order to get Batman's attention and use his new found techniques. They meet at an active volcano for the last act and their final dual...which I leave for you to discover. Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Birds of a Feather" it was the 47th produced and 52 to air. In this episode we see Veronica Vreeland at her wits end on why she is losing popularity amongst her rich friends. A friend reminds her of the time they attended a party where Joker robbed them blind, but since they're rich and don't care he says it was "a good giggle". Veronica says Joker is yesterdays news but then she looks at the paper and sees Penguin has been freed from Arkham. She hatches a plan where she'll invite him to her party freak people out. "If the planet were equitable, I'd still have my old job." The next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "What Is Reality?" it is the 48th produced and 45th to air. The Riddler is back, kinda. The Riddler has sent a huge Virtual Reality computer game to GCPD and he wants Batman and Robin to check it out. Alfred: Master Bruce, are you all right, sir?

Batman: I'm tired, Alfred.

Alfred: Well I shouldn't wonder, you've taken no meals today, and I can't recall when you last slept.

Batman: A weary body can be dealt with, but a weary spirit, that's something else. Sometimes, old friend, I wonder if I'm really doing any good out there.

Batman: I've put out a few fires yes, won a few battles, but the war goes on Alfred, on and on...

Today's BTAS episode is from the episode titled "I am the Night" it is the 49th produced and 34th to air. We start by seeing a weary, mentally broken Batman slumped in a chair honestly talking to Alfred about how he doesn't know if he's making any difference. He can win a few battles, put away a few criminals, but they just get out and repeat the cycle. Alfred is so concerned he has Robin try to talk to Batman, but he doesn't get through either. The only thing that eventually shakes him out of his funk is when Gordon becomes injured due to Batman being late to the scene of a crime. I always enjoyed this episode because, let's be honest, outside of being a normal human, we tend to not have too much in common with Batman. However, this episode shows even Batman gets tired, depressed, questions it all being worth it, and I know I personally can relate to times of feeling this way as I'm sure most can if we're truthful with ourselves. However, Batman is able to overcome these feelings of doubt and depression and returns to full form by the end of the episode. Have a great day.

The next BTAS episode is titled "Off Balance" it was the 50th produced and 44th to air. This episode starts with Batman asking an informant some questions but he's cut short by the mysterious Society of Shadows. Batman takes them on but before he can ask them questions they kill themselves with poisonous gas. He discovers that a villain named Vertigo wants to steal an ultrasonic drill from Wayne Enterprises and does so successfully. Batman starts the process of looking for him and heads for his castle. He joins up with Talia Al Ghul (although he doesn't know it) and together they get the drill and rid of Vertigo. Right when Batman thinks he's won the day Talia reveals who she is and takes the drill. Not before Batman alters the gun allowing it not to fire. Ras Al Ghul is impressed stating, "So even in defeat, the Detective manages to achieve some small measure of victory. As you said, Detective...'This is not over'." This episode is the first time we See Talia and Vertigo. Vertigo isn't seen again on this show but was in Young Justice and other animated properties as well as on Arrow! "Dear friends... today is the day the Clown cried...." The next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "The Man Who Killed Batman" it was the 51st produced and 49th to air. We see a frantic Sidney Debris allowed into Rupert Thornes office hoping for protection. Rupert Thorne needs no introduction he's heard of "Sid the Squid", the man who killed Batman. He goes into detail about how he killed Batman and we get to see it in flashback form. After we see his killing of Batman was dumb luck we see him put in jail. "You cured more than my body. You cured my heart." The next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Mudslide" and it is the 52nd produced and 63rd to air. Matt Hagen, Clayface, is back...but only because he's not able to compose his claylike body anymore. He's falling apart, losing himself more  each day. He enlist the aid of a doctor and medical consultant who used to work on movies with him, Stella Bates. She is in love with Hagen and has her own mental issues, not being able to discern fiction from real life. She watches movies of Hagen, which she uses as motivation to get him back to who he used to be. Hagen is happy to feed her delusion by quoting the lines from those movies to her in order to keep that motivation high. Both sick, but both feeding each other's illness. Clayface has to steal in order to get the chemicals he needs to stay one piece, and once Stella finds an actual cure he steals that. Batman's been on his trail and figured out Hagen and Stella's plan. They have a showdown in the rain on the edge of a cliff before Clayface takes a final bow, or so it seems, this is the last time we see Clayface in BTAS. Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "The Mechanic" it was the 55th produced and 48th to air. The episode starts off with us seeing Batman and Robin going after 3 of Penguins thugs, they get away and the Batmobile sustains major damage. The dynamic duo takes the car to a secret garage run by Earl Cooper and his daughter. He says he can fix it and gives Batman and Robin some motorcycles in the mean time. We than get taken to Penguins lair where an informant is telling Oswald that he's put together a list of parts the Batmobile would need based on the damage described, and has found that each of these parts were recently delivered to an Earl Cooper and they go after him. So again, the animated series leaving its mark on the Batman mythos. The next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Blind as a Bat" it is the 59th episode produced and 54th to air. The episode begins with Bruce Wayne at an event where they are testing a new Wayne tech helicopter, one with weapons even. It's not long before the Penguin hijacks it and opens fire on the crowd. "I am quite real. And as I'm sure you've realized by now, my reputation for resourcefulness is well deserved." Today's BTAS shot is titled "Quest of the Demon". The episode starts with Robin returning to his dorm room at Gotham U, out of no where he gets hit with a tranquilizer dart and from the shadows we see a masked man emerge. The next scene is Batman returning to the cave to tell Alfred he still has no lead on where Robin could be. Alfred looks concerned and heads up the house to leave Bruce alone for a bit. Bruce is alone until we see Ras Al Ghul and his guard Ubu come from nowhere, Bruce is pissed and demands to know who he is, but gets no answer. He shows Bruce pictures proving that his daughter Talia and Robin were taken on the same night and that he wishes to find them together, since he is the greatest detective. Batman can tell they are in or near Calcutta based on clues in the pictures, so they board Ras' plane and head there. Once there they encounter a group of assassin's that Batman takes down, he interrogates one and learns that Robin and Talia have been taken to Malaysia! Once in Malaysia Ras goes on they arrive at the temple where the kids are supposed to be Batman encounters a panther that he uses a sleeping gas bomb on, they then find a map of the Himalayas where they figure the kidnapper took Robin and Talia next, so off they go. Batman parachutes out of the helicopter they took and as soon as he does it gets hit with a rocket while Ras and Ubu were inside, so Batman continues on to find Robin, and take out some assassin's waiting. Once he did the man in the jackal masked appears and reveals himself to be Ras Al Ghul! He explains it was all a test, and then Talia shows up and Ras Al Ghul basically ask Batman to take his place when he passes and marry his daughter claiming the detective as the only one worthy. Batman declines and tries leaving but Ubu tries preventing him, but then Ras starts coughing and looking bad so they all rush him to the Lazarus pit, when he comes out he looks insane and he's  laughing like crazy...part 2 will continue the story. #rasalghul #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba

"As the great Lewis Carrol himself once said, 'One, two, one, two, through and through. And then the rope went snicker-snack. He left it dead and with its head, he went galumping back!'" The next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "The Worry Men" it's was the 65th produced and 65th to air. We start off by seeing Veronica Vreeland, who is throwing a party and talking to Bruce Wayne and other guest about her trip to South America. She explains that since she's been back and using her "Worry men" she's been feeling way less stressed and better overall. Bruce takes a look at a worry man, which looks like a tiny wooden figure but the he notices some men up in the skylight so he excuses himself and becomes Batman just in time to stop the would be theives. They get away however, when Batman saves some guest from a falling item. Batman returns home and shows Alfred the worry man and explains the story of the night before going to bed, Alfred actually slips the wooden figure under Bruce's pillow half kidding. In the morning Bruce learns that he's withdrawn millions of dollars from his own company, he has no memory of this and learns that others have done this to their companies as well.  He eventually sees they all attended Veronica's party so as Batman he tracks her down right as she's about to throw a briefcase of her money into the ocean. He takes her worry men and sees tiny microchips that he suspect must control brain waves...and he knows the Mad Hatter would do something just like this. He finds out where his hideout is and shows up to a room full of dolls of his Rogues gallery and fights off a bunch of them before coming face to face with the Madhatter! The rest I leave for you. "You said you could be yourself out here, remember? I guess that's what I was doing. Being myself." Today's BTAS shot is titled "Sideshow" and it is the 66th produced and 67th to make air. The episode opens with us being shown a train full of police transporting Killer Croc in chains to an upstate facility. Croc decides he's done playing nice, bites through the chains and starts the process of escaping. We see one of the police men run off opening his shirt to reveal Batman undercover. Croc gets hit with a heavy tranquilizer but still manages to handle Batman's attacks until they both fall off the train. They land hard after hitting a few tree branches, Croc picks up a huge rock to smash Batman's head but misses by inches due to the sedation, he then back pedals and falls off a cliff. Once he comes to again he continues walking until he falls into a river and his body gives out. He's saved by what looks to be a seal boy! Once he wakes up he sees he is in the midst of a "Freak show", people who go town to town showing off their oddities for money. They take in  Croc like one of their own, treating him great, he hears about a stash of money they have and he gets a new plan, take it. He traps all of the people at the camp, and when Batman shows up he's able to confine him as well. Will Croc finally succeed at a plan? You'll have to watch sometime and find out! "I used to believe Batman was responsible for you people but now I see nearly everyone here would of ended up exactly the same, Batman or no. Today's BTAS shot is from season 3 episode 12 titled "Trial". The episode starts with Pamela Isley being sentenced to Arkham and then we learn about Janet Von Dorn, the District Attorney, who believes Batman is a disgrace and responsible for creating these "super criminals" and states this on TV. Back at Arkham Harley welcomes back Ivy and tells her not to worry, right then, we see Mad Hatter is controlling the guards and soon Arkham is running wild. Batman and Janet both head there, separately of course. Janet gets easily apprehended and Batman gets tricked and knocked out. When he comes to he sees he is about to be put on trial for all he's done by a jury of Scarecrow, Harley Quinn, Mad Hatter, Riddler, Poison Ivy and Croc with The Ventriloquist as the bailiff and Harvey as the prosecutor. Janet, who hates Batman, is his defense and Batman must watch the whole thing play out with honorable Judge Joker residing over the proceedings. That's all I shall say as this episode is a must and you really need to see it yourself! "I'm truly sorry beloved, but he is my father..." Today's BTAS episode is titled "Avatar" which is the 69th episode produced and 68th aired. The episode starts with us being in Egypt around 1898. We see a young man lowered into a temple in order to retrieve artifacts. We see him enter a door that has a glowing light and then see that the men holding the rope are struggling to hold on and trying to bring the kid back. But when they see the end of the rope it's frayed and the boy gone. Flash forward to present day Gotham we see Lucius Fox commending Bruce on the new Egyptian artifacts he has put in his museum. One of them being a sacred scroll of Osiris, which happens to be the oldest Egyptian document. Later that night we see the museum empty and someone after the scroll, Batman shows up to find its Ubu, Ras Al Ghul's right hand man. Ras arrives and throws a cobra at Batman who gets bitten and must inject himself with an anti venom, allowing Ras to leave. Batman decides he's going to find Talia in order to find her father so he heads to Gibraltar. Talia helps, but hadn't heard from her father, she states the scroll is half of a map that leads to the tomb of the Egyptian queen Thoth Khepera. Ras is obsessed with finding it. Batman and Talia find the other half of the scroll but run into Ras. He goes on to tell why he's obsessed with the tomb, for Thoth Khepera had power over life and death which he desires to possess. He puts Talia and Batman in a trap and goes looking for the tomb. He eventually finds it and comes face to face with Thoth Khepera...what happens next is for you to see! "Look.. That's me in there, the real me! There I am. But it's not really real is it? Just made up and pretend..like my family and my life, and everything else! If I had to, like forced at gun point, pick a top 5... this would be in it. I love this episode because you really see how great Paul Dini is at writing and how he could make you so invested and care, even about a villain that looks as ridiculous as Baby Doll. The character may seem odd but this episode contains probably one of the, if not thee, saddest most human moments on the entire show or DC animated universe in my eyes. This episode should be on people's list of episodes right up there with Heart of Ice and Feat of Clay. If you haven't seen it or think I'm exaggerating..PLEASE go watch this and experience it for yourself if you haven't. It starts off silly but the episode will end with you just thinking, wow... "Red Claw?!" Today's BTAS episode is titled "The Lion and the Unicorn" it was the 77th produced and 85th to air. We start off with everything normal at Wayne manor until Alfred gets a call from his cousin Fredrick. He tells Alfred it's an emergency so Alfred leaves to London, England. When Batman and Robin see Alfreds note they piece together where he went and we learn Alfred was part of an intelligence agency while living in England. We then see Alfred in his home town but quickly chased and eventually apprehended by goons. He's taken to a room where's he's tied to a chair but with Fredrick. We then see who the master mind of all this is, Red Claw! She explains that she knows they have two parts of a code that unlock a nuclear bomb. She gives them truth serum and obtains it. Red Claw gets on television and threatens to use it unless paid a hefty ransom. Batman and Robin get there and confront her, but will they be able to prevent a nuclear explosion?  Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Harley's Holiday" it is the 81st produced and 76th to air. It's an episode that starts off with Harley in Arkham obtaining her certificate of Sanity. The next BTAS episode is titled "Deep Freeze" it is the 84th episode produced and 80th to air. A man named Grant Walker is after the key to immortality, and as the rich owner of a huge theme park he believes he has the funds to obtain it, he just needs the mind. He breaks Mr. Freeze out of Arkham and brings him to Oceania, his park. Mr. Freeze doesn't want to help Walker turn into the same being as he is, but Walker will show Victor he has the upper hand and reveals he has Nora Fries, his barely hanging on wife. Freeze relents and helps Grant. Batman and Robin, while looking for Freeze, get apprehended by Walkers drones. The duo are forced to watch Walker's transformation and hear how he will freeze Gotham in order to walk around without the aid of a suit. From there things go crazy, but that's for you to watch and enjoy. Will Freeze ever be reunited with Nora? and if so how? Batgirl: "You're the one who raised him." 
The next BTAS shot is from season 4 episode 5 titled "You Scratch My Back". It begins with us seeing Dick Grayson as Nightwing as he stakes out some gun runners. Batman and Batgirl show up and he becomes kind of annoyed, saying it's his gig. He excuses himself and goes after the thugs on his own. He starts taking them down but sees Batgirl and Batman helping. He sees one man tied up and gets really upset until seeing it was Catwoman that helped him and he's stunned. He continues to go after this gun running operation and while on the roof gets snuck up on by Catwoman who gives him a lot of info in order to try to be his partner, she manipulates Nightwing by saying she's changed and how Batman always treated her stern, just as he did Robin, preying on his emotions. She uses his desire to be on his own and prove himself to gain his trust and they go after the gang together. Until, that is, Nightwing sees that she's just after treasures she desires. Luckily Batman and Nightwing planned for this and they along with Batgirl need to take down the gun smugglers as well as get Catwoman. It's an awesome episode and really great we get to see the continuous growth of Dick Grayson as a character. #youscratchmyback #selinakyle #catwoman #barbaragordon #batgirl #brucewayne #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcuniverse #dcanimation #dcau #dcdirect #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #batmantheadventurescontinue #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham  #bigbadtoystore #soapstudioshk #nightwing #dickgrayson #robin #boywonder #thetylergshow #tylergshow

"Fear is the glue that holds society together. It's what makes people suppress their worst impulses. Fear is power. And today it will also be quite expensive... if you want the antidote." Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Never Fear" the 6th of the New Batman Adventures. It shows us the new design of the Scarecrow and what his newest plan is. He's got a guy fronting as a motivational speaker, convincing people he can make them more confident and happy with themselves, due to taking away their fear. In reality Scarecrow's toxin makes people more likely to do ridiculous reckless things, like walk on the ledge of a skyscraper, etc. Batman gets hit with this and becomes way too bold and Robin tries his hardest to keep him in check until having to bind him and go after Scarecrow alone. Robin catches up to the Master of Fear and sees he has the antidote he's trying to sell as a ransom. Tim tries to get it but is quickly apprehended, but luckily we see Batman's arrived. However, the Dark Knight still has no fear and grabs Scarecrow around the neck close to killing him! Robin gets the antidote and sprays Batman just in time, but that's just the beginning, the rest I leave for you! It's definitely a cool episode, I liked seeing a Batman with reckless abandon and the Scarecrow's redesign is actually one of the cooler ones. #neverfear #johnathancrane #thescarecrow #scarecrow #batmanandrobin #timdrake #robin #brucewayne #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcuniverse #dcmultiverse #dcicons #dcrebirth #dcanimation #dcau #dcdirect #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #batmantheadventurescontinue #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham  #bigbadtoystore #mcfarlanemultiverse #soapstudiohk #dioramaprints

"Hiya, Joker. If you're watching this tape, you've probably figured out you've been had. Yeah, I left you some dough, but only ten million, which, knowing you, you've already blown. See, I always hated your guts, and this was the perfect payback. By now you're probably out of real money, the I.R.S. is after you, and you can't admit I fooled you, or you'll be the laughingstock of the underworld. The joke's on you, sucker! I got the last laugh after all!" Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Jokers Millions" and it is the 7th of the New Batman Adventures. We start off seeing Harley and Joker stealing but being interrupted by Batman and Batgirl. The king and queen of Gotham get to their car but as they're driving the realize they're out of bullets and gas, due to their bad streak of luck and no funds. Joker gets away but Harley gets taken in. Once Joker gets back to his place we see he has a lot of bills piling up and his pet hyenas are starving. Then he sees a package with a tape from an old mob boss who recently died, King Barlowe, just left him $250 million! Joker immediately buys lawyers to clear his name, goes to clubs, golfs, and even holds tryouts for a new Harley. It isn't long, however, before something goes wrong, to find out what it is you must partake in mentally absorbing this episode through the visual medium for yourself. "Sometimes, there are no happy endings." Today's BTAS episode is titled "Growing Pains" and is the 8th of TNBA. It starts with Robin saving a girl named Annie from a biker gang. Robin thinks she's cute and tries talking to her but when he turns his back she's gone. Another day, while being driven from school by Alfred Tim spots Annie and goes after her. He starts to talk with her but realizes she has amnesia  and is struggling to remember where she's from. Robin decides to try to help her by taking her places she's been, trying to kickstart her memories, and it works, with a catch. She's a piece of Clayface, he was weak after the events of "Mudslide" and couldn't risk going to look for supplies on his own, so he made and sent Annie. This doesn't damper Robin though, he believes he can save her, but then Clayface arrives and the emotional stakes only rise from there, with the ending being quite tragic. Today's BTAS episode is titled "Mean Seasons" it's the 13th produced and 9th to air. It's a story about a beautiful supermodel, Paige Monroe, who had everything, the fame, money, and beauty. However, seasons passed and time was not forgiving. She couldn't get jobs anymore despite her surgeries in attempt to cling to youth. She dropped out of site for a few years and returned as Calendar Girl complete with mask hiding her ugly (in her mind) face. She quickly starts kidnapping the former agents she feels used her and threw her aside. Batman and Batgirl eventually foil her plan. At the last scene we see her without her mask, and she's as beautiful as she ever was and it's really sad to see. Mainly because you know she listened to what others told her instead of herself, dont let that kind of thing ruin you. Today's BTAS episode is titled "Animal Act" it's the 16th produced and 17th to air. It's a cool episode because it takes us back to the original Robin's roots as we go to Haley's Circus to investigate the recent use of animals in criminal acts. We even get taken to the good 'ol days as we see the original dynamic duo fight together twice as they take on a mad man controlling the animals. A very fun episode, and I think one that's often forgot. I know I tend to forget about it but as I watched I fell back in love with this one. I really really enjoyed just seeing Dick looking at a photo album of his family and longing for those days...but then seeing Batmans silhoutte appear across the pictures as his mentor's presence  reminds him of who he is now. Stuff like that makes this series second to none. Tomorrow is one of my favorite episodes from the New Batman Adventures titled "Old Wounds" as we take a look at why Batman and Robin had their falling out. "Quiet, Teekl. I want to savor this."
The next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "The Demon Within" it is the 18th episode and features Jack Kirby's Etrigan the Demon and Klarion the Witch Boy. It's a really fun episode due to the magic aspect, which this show didn't usually delve into. It's cool seeing any character done in Bruce Timm's style, but he really did a great job on how he did Etrigan, this figure is one of the cooler looking from the DC Collectibles line, to me. This episode was a tribute to "King" Jack Kirby. If you don't know who Jack Kirby is just Google him. I guarantee he's responsible for creating half the comic characters you love, hence his title as "King". There's a shot in this episode where Klarion wants cake and the name of the shop is "Kirby Cake Shop". All in all a very solid, fun and interesting episode. "'Cause I know what he's really like. And you guys are both totally clueless. First of all, Batman's real old, like, about 50. And second, Robin's a girl." Today's BTAS episode is titled "Legends of the Dark Knight" and is the 19th episode.  Easily a crown jewel of an episode in the 4th season, as it's one that's steeped in love and respect for the character. We see 3 young kids reading about an arsenist, Firefly, burning buildings for insurance, and they see a picture of a shadowy Batman as well. They all start talking about Batman and who they imagine he is, and what he's like. That's where we start getting glimpses of different versions of Batman and we see different Easter eggs also showing the love for all the iterations of the character. The next BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Mad Love" and it's the 21st episode of The New Batman Adventures. Remember all the way back in season 1 where we first saw Harley in "Joker's Favor"? Remember thinking, "I wonder why she hangs around with a crazy psychopathic mass murdering clown?" Well...this episode answers it all. Watching this now makes me think, there's no way this episode would make air today! It's dark and delves into an issue and type of relationship that is not one that should be emulated and one that was definitely not portrayed in the Suicide Squad movie. That Joker was a lovesick puppy dog and looks like a Teddy bear next to this episode and Joker. It's a fan favorite for a reason though. It's a great story, answers questions, we see Harley learn she can get Batman on her own, and we see an unflinching depiction of a relationship no one should aspire to have. 🦇 #madlove #harleyquinn #harleenquinzel #thejoker #joker #dccollectibles #alexross #dcuniverse #dcmultiverse #dcanimation #dcau #dcdirect #dioramaprints  #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #batmantheadventurescontinue #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham #mcfarlanemultiverse #soapstudioshk #brucetimm #pauldini #kevinconroy #markhamill #arleensorkin #jokersunday

Bruce Wayne: Everything's changed for me in the past few weeks. The pain of my parents' deaths... It's still there, but it seems smaller. And there's a new feeling now.

Barbara Gordon: Which would be?

Bruce Wayne: It's a lightness. A sense that things will work out for the best.

Tim Drake: It's called happiness.

Bruce Wayne: Whatever it is, I like it. And I know who's responsible for it. I've asked Susan to marry me. She's accepted. She's everything I need. She's perfect.

Dick Grayson: There's just one problem. That.

*nods at the batsuit*

Dick Grayson: How you gonna keep it from her?

Bruce Wayne: I won't have to. I've always assumed that sooner or later the three of you would get all this. Well, it's going to be sooner. I'm not going to be Batman anymore.

The next BTAS episode is titled "Chemistry" and is the 22nd produced and 21st TNBA episode  to air. It's a plot that is somewhat similar to Mask of the Phantasm. Bruce attends a wedding where he catches the garder, takes a picture with the woman who caught the bouquet and they spark a relationship. Bruce is absolutely head over heels for her and even calls a Batfamily meeting letting Dick, Barbara, and Tim know he's getting married and that they will have to carry on without him. Soon after he's married though things start to get weird, it's not till he's on his honeymoon cruise that he pieces everything together. Poison Ivy built perfect companions from plants to match up with the social elite. Soon after getting her plant creations to fool the rich targets she'd kill the spouse and have her plant creatures take the estate, and then she'd take the money for herself. Batgirl and Robin reach Bruce in time, bringing his suit, and a battle ensues, which is for you to see. She catches Batman with a vine, poisons him, and explains she did it because Harvey built a penitentiary in a spot where a rare rose grew, and she only saved a precious few. Batman tries escaping while starting a fire in the green house, he's seemingly beat, he sees Ivy loom over him in a drugged daze, will he escape? How? "Remember what you told me? You can't lose hope.." Today's BTAS episode is from season 1 the 8th to be produced and 23rd to air. We start off with Bruce volunteering his time to feed homeless at the dock rescue mission, which he also gives money too. As he's working, a priest mentions that a lot of homeless are missing. Bruce decides to investigate, dying his hair gray, and growing out some stuble he assimilates himself into the homeless community and starts asking questions. Before he knows it he's knocked out and taken to a chain gang camp where Boss Biggis runs a brutal business, using these slaves for cheap labor. Bruce has amnesia and has totally forgotten who he even is! He struggles with this identity lose while trying to get used to the slave labor. He has a dream one night where he's walking down a hall and the Joker grabs him and they fall off a building. Then his dream takes him to the dock rescue mission. He walks the street as Bruce Wayne and a homeless man comes up and ask for a few bucks, so he obliges. Then a few more homeless come and he keeps handing out money generously until he's overwhelmed by beggars and he slumps his shoulders..shedding a tear. Knowing that as much as he can do, it's barely enough to help. It's quite a striking visual and in media we see Batman as a loner, or someone that doesn't love people. On the contrary, this episode shows Bruce has a huge heart for those less fortunate than himself and he strives to help them. Again, it's one I wasn't fond of as a child, because he's barely in costume and no big rogues villain. The writing, striking visuals, and different way of telling this story makes it a winner in my book now. "This is how I shall always remember you: surrounded by winter, forever young, forever beautiful. Rest well, my love. The monster who took you from me will soon learn that revenge is a dish... best served cold." 
The next BTAS episode is the 14th produced, 3rd to air, and it needs no introduction, "Heart of Ice". Every so often we as fans of comics and their tie ins get treated to a story that feels bigger then the rest. As Batman fans we've been treated to a lot, Death in the Family, Killing Joke, Knightfall, Dark Knight Returns, Under the Red Hood, Flashpoint, Endgame, etc, you catch my drift... stories that are game changers. Well, when you mention Batman the Animated Series, outside of Kevin Conroy and Mark Hamill's perfect portrayals of their characters, I'm pretty sure most fans have this episode come to mind. It's a beautifully haunting tragedy of a man who unfairly lost his wife and just wanted to save her. I think when this episode aired every one stopped and took notice that this show was not some silly thing for kids, but was meant to be something more and stand the test of time, which it has. It's not my personal favorite, but I can't deny it's almost a perfect episode and reinvigorated a character most thought idiotic. "Help stop it Stromwell, all your power and money has bought you is an empire of misery. It has to stop Stromwell, it has to stop now." Today's BTAS episode is from season 1, the 12th to be produced but 6th to air titled "Its Never Too Late" This episode shows us Arnold Stromwell, an aging crime boss at war with Rupert Thorne for Gothams underground. The war is amplified due to Stromwell's son missing. Stromwell, of course, believes this to be the work of Thorne as a taunt to him, so he takes a meeting with him. On the way to this meeting Stromwell passes a rail road train station and we see a flashback that shows him stealing as a youth with a friend, Michael. Michael seems very responsible and gets onto "Arnie" for his theft letting him know it will catch up to him, but Stromwell was too proud even back then. Young Stromwell plays on the tracks and his shoe gets caught as a trains coming and..then we go back to present-day. Stromwell has a talk with Thorne but he hasnt seen his kid, Thorne flees leaving Stromwell in the restaurant with a bomb, but he's saved by Batman. Batman has sympathy for him, and takes him to his son who is at a drug rehab center. This gets Arnold furious saying he'll kill whoever got him hooked. His ex-wife replies, "Look in the mirror" The flashback memory of his train encounter, almost being blown up, seeing his son in a rehab hospital with his ex wife pointing out his drugs and lifestyle were responsible send Stromwell out of the room devastated. Batman then gives the quote above to Arnold, basically letting him know it's not too late to fix things. Stromwell however doesnt listen and back stabs Batman while looking for records to give to the GCPD. Rupert Thorne shows up and Batman has to subdue him and his men which he does. Stromwell we see has ran and he's st the train station and we see the rest of the flashback. He went from one track to the next, narrowly escaping once, but the train comes around a bend and is heading right for him when his friend Michael pushes him out of the way sacrificing himself for his friend. Definitely another powerful episode and quite possibly the most adult of them all.

Lloyd Ventrix: So what if it is? I don't care! As long as I have it, I can take my daughter back whenever I want! Her mother won't be able to stop me, and neither will you!

Today's BTAS episode is from season 1 titled "See No Evil" it was the 56th to air but 17th to be produced. The episode starts with us seeing a an invisible man go into a little girl named Kimmy's bedroom. She greets him as Mojo and they talk, "Mojo" says he'll see her soon but she warns they're moving, and this upsets him. We hear Kimmy's mom coming and Mojo leaves, the mother thinks the daughter really has an imaginary friend so she pays her no mind. We then see the man "Mojo", and his real name is Lloyd Ventrix. He puts on this silver suit, hits a button turning invisible and then proceeds to rob a jewelry store. Bruce is there and quickly changes into Batman and then goes after the invisible man. He is able to find a few tricks in order to see Lloyds silhouette, but the invisibility is too much for Batman as he gets whooped. Llyod escapes to rob another day. Batman does some digging to find out who the man is, and in the process learns the plastic that makes the plastic invisible is also highly toxic to the wearer. Batman goes after Lloyd as he is abducting Kimmy who we learn is his daughter, and his ex-wife has a restraining order on him as well. Batman confronts him and is able to take him down while keeping Kimmy safe. Very cool and different episode, crazy to see how an ordinary guy in an invisibility suit can give Batman so much trouble. #seenoevil #lloydventrix #cloakofinvisibility #invisibilitycloak #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #batmantheadventurescontinue #brucetimm #pauldini #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcanimation #dcau #dcicons #dcrebirth #dcanimateduniverse #dc #bigbadtoystore #beastkingdom #soapstudioshk #mcfarlanemultiverse #mcfarlane #mattelmultiverse #mattel

"You know as a kid I used to watch you, with my father. The Gray Ghost was my hero..." Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Beware the Gray Ghost" it was the 18th produced and 32nd to air. Masterpiece, this episode is that, in my eyes. Anytime we get a glimpse into Batman's past or childhood it's cool, because we still have not seen that too much, at least at the point in time this aired. We see a very meta scene where we are watching Bruce Wayne and his father watch their favorite hero on TV, The Gray Ghost! This scene alone is amazing to me. We already love Batman because we can relate to him, and here we see he's a lot more like us then we initially ever thought. The story progresses to where Bruce, as Batman, gets to meet and help his hero in real life, Simon Trent aka the Gray Ghost. Adam West voices the Gray Ghost, and if you know anything about his life you can see this episode does not try to hide the parallels of reality and fiction when it comes to West's struggle to find work after being type cast as only Batman. This is indeed a crown jewel for this series and another example of how this show elevated itself beyond the norm of what everyone else was doing at the time. "Matt? Matt is that you? What in heavens name did they do to ya?" Today's BTAS episode is titled "Feat. of Clay" part 1 and it's one half of my absolute favorite episode(s) of the series! I think everything about it is perfect. It draws you in right away seeing Bruce Wayne set up Lucious Fox leaving us just as confused as Lucious! We find out it was Matt Hagan, a man who suffered a terrible accident to his face. He then got taken advantage of by being given a miracle product which temporarily allowed him to fix his deformity. This came at a price, however,  that of doing illegal jobs for Roland Dagget. Hagan realizes he can't just be doing temporary doses of this stuff and in order to get a lot he breaks into Dagget industries. Dagget's goons grab him, and force him to ingest gallons of the clay turning him into Clayface. During all this we see Batman in full detective mode trying to clear Bruce Wayne's name before being brought into jail. We then see Matt's friend Teddy looking for Hagan and finding him in an alley, but not the same Hagan. "Good people still live in Crime Alley." The next  BTAS episode is from season 1 titled "Appointment in Crime Alley" and it was 12th to air but 26th produced. Batman took on gentrification long before the hipsters started taking over Brooklyn. In this episode Roland Daggett wants to destroy crime alley so he can get all the poor people and business' out of there and build up his business in their place. He hires an arsonist named Nitro to do the job, severing himself from guilt. He also starts sending flunkies around Crime Alley telling people to clear out, Batman arrives to prevent two thugs from harassing a mom and girl. He learns about them strong arming people out and does more investigation on who hired them. The whole reason Batman was in Crime Alley was for an appointment with Dr. Leslie Thompkins, she notices he's late so goes looking for him but accidentally sees Nitro the arsonist and crew about to start burning down everything. She speaks up, confronting them and is immediately tied up to a chair in a room full of explosives. Batman finds out Thompkins is missing while looking for him so he goes for her by heading to her house. There he finds a scrapbook of his parents murder, with a picture of Dr. Thompkins holding and comforting a young, devastated Bruce. Nitro does start to burn some buildings but nothing great and is stopped by Batman easily, he confesses who he's working for, but Daggett gets off, he's too powerful. Batman decides he will let this go for now, as he meets up with Dr. Thompkins and they visit Bruce's parents murder site, the episode closes with Leslie comforting Bruce again as they remember Thomas and Martha. #appointmentincrimealley #rolanddaggett #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcanimation #dcanimateduniverse #dcau #dcicons #dcrebirth #dceu #lesliethompkins #thomaswayne #marthawayne #thomasandmarthawayne #crimealley #brucewayne #brucetimm #pauldini #arkhamasylum #arkhamknight #arkham #bigbadtoystore #soapstudioshk #dioramaprints

The Mad Hatter: Now just a moment! You don't want to do anything foolish! This isn't an ordinary dream! What if you're wrong?

Bruce Wayne: Then I'll see you in your nightmares!

Today's BTAS shot is from the episode titled "Perchance to Dream" it is the 30th produced and 26th to air. This episode has always been really close to being my number 1 and it may even be 1b behind the "Feat of Clay" episodes. The entire episode has you on the edge of your seat wondering what's going on, and you're kind of confused the entire time, sort of like a real dream. Bruce Wayne wakes up one morning to find everything in his life is perfect. He's not Batman, he's engaged to Selina Kyle, and his parents are alive and in great health, perfection! But just how we the audience know something's not quite right, Bruce feels it too. He feels Batman has something to do with it so he goes to a patrol spot at a bell tower he usually goes to nightly. There Bruce confronts the imposter and eventually removes the mask revealing Mad Hatter! The episode only gets better from there with the writing  being prime BTAS, creating stories that just fire on all cylinders. Batman fans were spoiled with this one, all time classic. "I've waited a loooong time." The next BTAS episode is titled "Robin's Reckoning Part 2" it's the 32nd/33rd to be produced and 51st/53rd to air. In this episode we see the origin of Robin/ Dick Grayson. We see his parents death at the hands of Tony Zucco at Haley's Circus. Bruce happened to be in attendance and decided he was going to adopt young Grayson. We see Bruce eventually reveal he's Batman and start the relationship of the original dynamic duo. Only one problem, Bruce has hidden who killed Robins parents from Dick to protect him from acting out violently in a rage towards the man and do something he would regret. Robin finds this out though while being left behind and goes after Zucco himself. He eventually finds him and the scene is filled with emotion. You see Robin in full on wreck mode as he drags Zuccos body like a rag doll while on his motorcycle. He then whoops him up a bit then dangles him near the edge of a pier. As he speaks you hear pure anger/rage as he looks into the fearful eyes of his parents murderer. One more push and he could end Zucco, but Batman gets to him and talks him out of his emotional rage. The episode ends with Zucco in jail and Robin doing the right thing. It's a well crafted, emotional episode that is beautifully done because it wasn't rushed and they expanded it to the two parts, highly recommended this one. #dccollectibles #dccomics #dcuniverse #dcmultiverse #dcanimation #dcanimateduniverse #dcau #dc #batmantheanimatedseries #batmantas #btas #thenewbatmanadventures #tnba #robinsreckoning #robinsreckoningpart2 #tonyzucco #thedynamicduo #dynamicduo #batmanandrobin #dickgrayson #theflyinggraysons #robin #theboywonder #boywonder #brucetimm #pauldini #bigbadtoystore

"So, the famous Batman, I am honored!" Today's BTAS episode is titled "Night of the Ninja" it was 35th produced and 28th to make air. Wayne Entriprises has been a major target of thefts all the sudden, being attacked often and Batman decides he's going to find out who's helping themselves. He comes to find a Ninja, that he takes on and is beating until he fights dirty, Batman is almost taken out until Robin saves him. During the fight the Ninja suffered a tear in the back of his shirt and Bruce  clearly sees the tattoo of his rival from when he trained in Japan. His name is Kyodai Ken, he was superior to Bruce back then and regularly beat him in sparring matches. One night while training late Bruce caught Kyodai trying to steal from the sensai, this caused Kyodai great shame and he was kicked out, he vowed vengeance on Bruce...and all these years later he is getting it. Kyodai kidnaps Bruce and Summer Gleeson spelling out his plan. He fights Bruce but Bruce holds back in front of Summer, taking a major beating to hide the fact he's Batman. Robin shows up, covers Gleeson's face and Bruce proceeds to completely dominate Kyodai. Kyodai manages to get away, and we will see him again later. "Getting a little fresh air? How come I wasn't invited to this little get together?." The next BTAS shot is from the 2 part episode titled "Heart of Steel" they were the 38-39th episodes produced and 39-40th to be aired. The episode starts with us seeing Wayne Enterprises shut down for the night when all of a sudden a briefcase with metal legs and mechanical eye start going through Wayne's computers obtaining information. The guards are no match but Batman shows up. We quickly see he's no match either as the robot gets away with the information and sends it in the form of a rocket to a woman on the beach. Batman is in his glider following the car she got in but is shot down. We later find out the robot stole "wetware" which are computer chips allowing machines to think on their own. Bruce knows the only man who could build things like that is Karl Rossum. Bruce goes to pay him a visit, but he swears he knows nothing about it. Then, he shows Bruce his newest and best invention: H.A.R.D.A.C. (Holographic Analytical Reciprocating DigitAl Computer), true artificial intelligence. Right then Rossum's assistant, Randa Duane, comes out. She looks kinda familiar, and shakes Bruce's hand, he notices it's cold as ice but she says she was in the cold room. Bruce takes her out on a date to get information out of her but while he does H.A.R.D.A.C. starts replacing people with robots, starting with Jim Gordon! Randa also bugs the batcave discovering Bruce Wayne's identity!
